		(uuid "2564aefc-6e67-423d-bf17-be08008a45c9")
	)
	(text "This example circuit uses another Q43 PIC as a slave device.  The address of the slave \nis determined using RC0..2 inputs. Port A is the input switches, and port D\nis the output LED display.  The slave generates an interrupt on change on port \nRB0 pin if any of the inputs change value.  A smaller PIC device can be used \nas well depending on the inputs that need to be scanned or monitored \nas well as outputs desired.  A smaller pic device could be used (such \nas a PIC 12 or PIC 16 family) especially if an I/O extender (such as \nthe MCP23x17 or MCP23x08) are utilized.  PIC 12 devices generally only\nhave one I2C port, requiring the use of bit-banged I/O for the second \nI2C interface if an I/O expander is used."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 21.844 154.94 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "55ff0040-2edc-40fd-8de0-3d53e21435ac")
	)
